reviews.text: The only regret I had was not being able to read the stories on every gravestone in the Bellefontaine Cemetery. The cemetery is very well maintained and the most beautiful cemetery I've ever been! I can't wait to come visit again.

This is maybe my favorite place in the city. I once saw "The other forest park" written on an event sign there. In my opinion it is "The better Forest Park." As an avid history and architecture enthusiast I'm in heaven(pardon the expression) at this cemetery. Shockingly beautiful and just plain cool!

A beautiful cemetery with an arboretum. Quiet and large enough to have privacy. They provide  free services for families dealing with the loss of a newborn which is a kindness and a load off of a terrible loss.
Beautifully kept, tons of history! They do tours which tell you of all the wonderful history. Plus if you are a geocacher there are numerous geocaches.

Took a tour  of the  a Level II Accredited Arboretum  and learned history of St. Louis.  Bellefontaine has an accessible and diverse horticultural collection, and has become an important natural sanctuary and habitat for wildlife in the urban environment. It is the only accredited arboretum in the city of St. Louis.

I found that the Bellefontaine’s grounds are home to an international variety of meticulously cared-for trees and shrubs, providing a changing landscape every season. Until the mid-twentieth century, Bellefontaine Cemetery was home to a greater variety of trees than the Missouri Botanical Garden. I learned that they have over 1,100 shrubs and over 5,000 trees represent over 200 distinct varieties.

properties.formatted_address: 5239 W Florissant Ave, St. Louis, MO 63115, USA
properties.name: Calvary Cemetery & Mausoleum

reviews.text: Calvary Cemetery & Mausoleum has long history. I am Catholic and all of my family is buried there and I will be too. It's exciting see all the good reviews about it. For the bad reviews, I'm very disappointed. You say it's in the hood. You have to understand  and remember the area before there was a hood there. If you don't like it have your family members exhumed and relocated. Bet you don't have the money to do so. Your not respecting your loved ones. I'm sure Mr. Dred Scott is comfortable there like I will be when the time comes to rest next to my mother and  grandmother and family members.

Calvary Cemetery and Mausoleum is an amazing place to take a walk and learn some history, especially if you pair it with Bellefontaine Cemetery next door. There are quite a few famous names like Dred Scott, William Tecumseh Sherman, and Tennessee Williams and standing next to their graves is incredibly powerful. I recommend pulling up their Wikipedia pages and reading them aloud while next to their graves.

This cemetery has ornate metal signs posted everywhere, overhanging the curb. If you pull over to let another car pass, as I did, you can very easily end up with a deep scrape on your car, as I did. Totally unnecessary and should be replaced with round signs slightly set back from the road, like Bellefontaine. A 5 minute visit to the Garden of Innocents costs me $500+ in auto body repair.

My father just passed away and I called Calvary Cemetery to find out about getting a plaque placed next to his parents, who are memorialized there on, or near, the grave of my great grandfather. The person I spoke with told me that I had to prove I was a direct descendant of the person who held the account for the family plot. He gave me her name, but I have never heard of her before. I mentioned that if my great grandfather and both my grand parents are either buried or memorialized there, how could I not be a direct descendant of the person whom he claimed held the family plots? Well, It turns out she is my great, great grandmother. So, I need to contact her to get permission. Does anyone know of a good app to communicate with those existing in the great beyond? As I've been taking care of the odds and ends of my father's passing, I've been greeting with nothing but empathy from people at organizations I've contacted — with this one exception. I suppose the man who I talked with could have been having a bad day — although, I don't see how it can be worse than the past few days I've had. My advice to people who run Calvary Cemetery is to at least act like you care. It seems like that's your business. And the guy who I spoke to was very, very bad at his job.

Calvary Cemetery is in the very top for cemeteries in St Louis and the 2nd oldest in the Archdiocse. Its beauty surrounds you the minute you drive through the gate. There are some of the most unique and spectacular monuments you'll want to see. Bring your walking shoes because it's huge, over 400 acres. There are also several well known families buried here. Beautiful in all seasons to visit.

reviews.text: Our family has had a grave site at SS Peter&Paul since 1973.  We have a large site along the perimeter of the cemetery's border with an alley. A couple of years ago we discovered that a car had apparently crashed through the chain link fencing around the cemetery on that border and knocked over our headstone.  The car left a black mar on the back of the 6' headstone as evidence of the event. The cemetery had afixed the large headstone back onto it's pedestal, but the damaged fencing and shrubbery were still present.  I called the cemetery and issued a complaint and corrective action request to prevent future damage to our gravesite from another such incident.  The ensuing discussions were with the head caretaker at the cemetery.  To keep this short, he was most responsive and followed through on everything he said they would do.  I'd give him a 5 star that's for sure.  I put 4 down because I think someone from the cemetery management should have reached out to us when the damage occurred. That did not happen See the corrective action the cemetery performed in the pics below.  We are happy with it.  Word to others, your homeowners insurance is very limited dollar wise for claims against it for headstone replacement. Ours would have only covered about a tenth the value of replacement had the headstone been broken.

My in laws are buried there. They bought 4 plots in their early 20’s. Both sets of my husbands grandparents are buried there also. They would be in their 90’s now. You would think being a Catholic Cemetery it would be better taken care of. Perpetual care is a joke. The grass is never taken care of. My in laws have a flat stone and from a distance it looks like a hole, you can’t see the headstone because it hasn’t been trimmed in a long time. So when we go out to put a flower on all 3 graves we take out trimmer and trim the 3 plots. We shouldn’t have to do this. The Archdiocese should be a shamed of themselves.
Beautiful old Cemetery, very well kept with amazing statues.

I tried to find my grandparents grave, the website said the plot 37 so I walked every I'll in that plot and could not find them because it doesn't give a location on the website for them nobody at the office ever answer the phone so I had a hard time trying to find them this is my 3rd attempt in the cemetery in a week to try to find them Kama sham On jusaint Peter and Saint Paul cemetery for not responding back to people's phone calls when there trying to find their loved ones
Needs a little work

reviews.text: Very pretty cemetery. Older gravestones but still well cared for. I live nearby and walk through it sometimes. There are victims of the cholera pandemic, WWI, etc. Some of the stones have cracked or fallen into disrepair, but the cemetery is always mowed and clean when I've come through.

This cemetery is in terrible condition with the number of toppled stones due to vandalism by homeless people sleeping in the cemetery, mower damage by city workers or contractors, excess dirt not being removed from new grave sites and the graves haphazardly backfilled by contractors and dead trees, marked for removal several years ago,  allowed to fall on their own damaging stones or blocking roads in the cemetery. Attempts to get help from aldermen have fallen on deaf ears.
So many of the headstones are toppled over, covered by trees, the grass isnt well maintained, it's a mess, truly saddening
Very old stones and statues but very unkept

reviews.text: This place doesn’t even deserve a star. It is very difficult to get in contact with anyone. They only answer for funeral homes to collect payment.  I’ve been waiting on Rik to contact me for more than two years now.  I paid a foundation fee to have my great grandpa headstone put down in 2017 and here it is 2020 and the headstone is still not in the foundation.  I’ve been calling and calling and only get a response through text saying their “ busy” or for me to just contact BBB or a lawyer.  Please DO NOT bury any of your loved ones at this trashy, unprofessional cemetery.  There is no dignity.  Your loved ones deserves a better final resting place where if the family have any issues or question they contact someone.

What has happened to this cemetery? I attended a burial two years ago and it was spotless.  I attended a burial September 21, 2016 and it doesn't look like the same place.  The grass was unkempt, trees have been cut down and left to lay on graves; tree limbs laying all around the grounds; the American Flag at the burial site was worn and tattered.  I was appalled.

My mother is buried there.  I dont have a tombstone on her grave , but they went and buried someone on top of my mother grave.  I know that they should have seen her casket there before they put another one there.  Makes me wonder if caskets are buried in the ground. Someone is going to have to do sone explaining to me and my lawyer.

Very run down. No one is ever available to talk to. They don't keep it clean like they use to. Stuff keeps getting stolen from my nephew grave. I have family in that cemetery since the early 1900. Who ownes this place?
Need to keep better records, trying to find a relatives grave from the 1800’s and they tell my he’s not there, after reading some of these reviews I understand why

reviews.text: Beautiful, very well keep. From ornate monuments, to the simplistic, they have it all. If you like old Cemetery Statues they have it. The staff is absolutely amazing. They will lead you right to the well known people interned within the Cemetery. Extremely friendly and helpful.

Such wonderful staff . I Had my babygirl May 12 , 1995 , She passed July 23 , 1995 from A. I. D. S. Her dad and I had her buried here . She's in a spot called babyland , it was the last spot open at the time , she's buried under a shade tree with all the other babies buried there . The staff helped make the burial easy , they made you feel welcomed , needed , they was friendly , caring , thoughtful .

My mom 2006, aunt 2012, and  baby cousin 1987 are buried here.  I visit them often/or leave mementos.
Everytime I visit, the grounds are beautifully kept.  They have perpetual care and they follow through and  in inform loved ones when items will be removed if you want to retrieve.  The staff are ALWAYS working hard and caring  for the grounds.  Once I got a there alittle late  one cold winter evening was a little afraid to be out there alone, and one of the grounds men must have sensed it, came and said hello, helped me clean the leaves, got back on his tractor and he stayed until I finished all 3 graves.  I will always remember that and thank him.

The Consulting staff are VERY compassionate, comforting, patient and helpful.  Provides guidance when needed when the family is lost in in making rational decisions, never pushy, explains everything clearly.

If you have a problem with headstones. they get right on it.  We are very happy our loved ones are with St. Peters.  Thank🙏🏾 you all.

What an amazing cemetery! I went just to photograph the cemetery and their statues. I had read in the review before I went that they were very helpful. And that they were. At one point I believe they thought I was lost and stopped to offer me help. I let them know I was not and in return let them know how beautiful the grounds were kept up. The man just bowed his head as a gracious gesture. Absolutely beautiful place with great staff.

My mother has been buried here since 1992.  The grounds are always immaculate.  The staff is friendly and helpful.  My father is now buried there and I am hopeful that when my day comes that I can be laid to rest in such a peaceful setting.

He asked my name four times(to which I told him each time) and asked why I was calling and what I wanted. Despite my repeating  ' I'm calling for information on burying my father. Can you help me and tell me the process?'. This Lemay trash needs to be buried there himself. He was drunk or off his medication.

I don't understand why is it taking over a year to get a headstone no one will call you back. I asked for proof that it was made and he couldn't give me any proof. I want my dad's headstone or money back ASAP. I paid for it over a year ago

reviews.text:
They scammed me at such a hard time.

When my dad died he had no plans, this is where my aunt said she thought he had family and would be the best option. Michael Flannigan advised me on which site to purchase. I only had hours to make the decision and expressed how important and up right headstone was. He insisted that I had to buy atleast 2 plots to do so…. Now a few months later after speaking with office staff, I found out there is a two sided headstone spot available for 1/3 of the cost.  I could move him from his current place of rest, at of course a cost if it’s that important to me or buy the other plots. Michael should be ashamed of himself and buyer beware if choosing to lay a loved one here.

Picture of open spot

For the past couple of years Flowers and decorations have been having legs and walking away. I know the office can not do much about it. I feel that my family that we can not have nice things on my family's plot. I come there monthly to visit so it not like they sit there long. The reason I am publishing it so others know the situation is here at Resurrection.
Please correct your hours as I drove to Resurrection Cemetery arriving about 3:55 pm & as I arrived at the entrance, I heard the door being locked. Your web site info states the closing time as 5 pm.

One of my loved ones is buried here. Grounds are always  well kept when I visit  and I  have never had a problem or issue. Only thing I dont like seeing is the giant homes being built across from the cemeterty.

The cemetery itself is fine. However when our service arrived to bring my mother's casket it was like dropping her off at the curb literally! Why is this! They put a casket stand at the curb instead of up further where she was to be buried! Why didn't we see her casket being lowered and why no tent or area for our family! We were rushed off by the man from the funeral home, he came up to me and said they are waiting for you all to leave so they can bury her. We were trying to say last goodbyes at take flowers from her casket! So rude! We paid$1300 for the grave opening and closing they need to show some respect!

reviews.text: One of my favorite cemeteries to visit. We always stop by and say hi to the Alvarez sisters who died in the early 1900s. More than a hundred years since their deaths and they still get visitors. Very serene and we almost always see deer.

We were very fortunate to have had everything pre-planned for my mother’s funeral. Kim at Hoffmeister South Chapel assisted me in planning everything. She was excellent and very knowledgeable of everything that needed to be selected. She made a lot of the decisions I had to make seem effortless. Highly recommend Kim to assist you!  After my mother passed I was contacted by John Mitnik, he continued to help assist me in preparing for the funeral. It was not an easy task as a day before the funeral we got 8 inches of snow. I couldn’t get to the funeral home to make the final arrangements so John and I did most of the selection of music, flowers and all of the final touches by telephone.
With the assistance of Laine Hamstra he drove to my home and picked up my mother’s clothes, pictures and everything I needed to sign, I can’t thank him enough for doing that, my family was very thankful. So yes I would definitely give Hoffmeister and Mt Hope a 10+, they made the day perfect.  Thank you!!
Cyndi Weir, Laine Hamstra and the entire staff of Mt. Hope were very professional and sincerely caring during this difficult time.   We all truly appreciated how they went over and beyond.
A beautiful historic cemetery. I just can't say enough good things about it.
I buried my partner there. You couldn't ask for better people than the folks there in your time of need. Truly outstanding.

Meanwhile for Perpetual care that cemetery is the worst I've ever seen in my life. Gravestones toppled over and broken branches in the road Grass a foot high it's awful absolutely awful. I live in South Carolina I have never been in a cemetery in South Carolina that was anywhere near as Despicable as this one is I cannot move my grandparents so they will stay there for the rest of their life but God help anybody else that wants to go into that Cemetery it is not for the faint of heart

This cemetery is a disgrace I hate that my mother has to be there,but this was her wishes because her family is there. My mother has been there for 6 months and her grave still is not filled in .The man at desk said it would be taken care of but hasn't and the grass was a foot tall I pulled the weeds around her grave site myself,you can step down it the site in some spots that's how much dirt needs to be filled in.It literally makes me cry everytime I visit.

This place is horrible

He then up'd and move from St Louis, MO to sunny 🌞 California were he met me 14 years later. My mother among many other family and friends rest here. The only issue I have with them is my mother's flowers as well as solar lights were ran over by a vehicle and destroyed. That really 🤬me the 🤬 off. They were notified and nothing was done.  Now I don't put things there that I really would like  because I feel that someone might steal or break it....

We had to tear away the vegetation on several before finding the right ones.  I was appalled at the condition, and made a complaint at the office.  The response was that they would trim around the family graves.  Much more than that is needed.  The cemetery seems to be going downhill rapidly.

The only reason I’m given one star because you have to!! The upkeep of this cemetery is terrible! The grass is never cut! Every time I go to visit my mom and grandmother my husband have to bring his trimmer! To cut around their headstones! I have spoke with Eric several times about this issue! His attitude is so nonchalant! No compassion about the issue! I’m going to keep complaining and reaching out to the BBB Tell tell someone do something about this situation!!
Please if you’re reading this do not bury your love ones at this cemetery!!!

reviews.text: My mother was buried here a year ago and we have been trying to get her stone placed ever since. We paid in full for the stone, but have received the run around since day one. I've been told multiple times that the stone will be there on a certain date and it doesn't arrive. No communication to say that it hadn't arrived until I email Alicia, the "general manager". Then it's a miscommunication and the stone "will be there" on another date...again it doesn't arrive. Thankfully she was buried in a family plot so we know where she is, unlike some of the other reviewers, but you would think that the owners would be more expedient and focused on helping their families lay their loved ones to rest without the immense amount of turmoil that has been experienced during this process. It is unprofessional, not compassionate at all and borderline inhumane for those just trying to find peace. Do better!
This is a beautiful Cemetery with some very beautiful old monuments as well as new. Well keep in the winter.

This is Avery beautiful cemetery. Buried my mom in 1/15, every time me and my sister go it seems that she's been moved over will find her things that was placed  on her head stone on somebody's else head stone. The staff always have a reason why things are always moved. It hurts my heart so bad to not having her now it's really broken too think she might not be in this spot.

I am very disturbed ! My brother was buried there in September 2018. I went there in January 2019 to order a stone and put flowers on his gravesite . When I asked to see my brother's gravesite..the only thing they could show me was a huge pile of dirt in an area about a 40 ft by 40 ft and said your brother is somewhere in this area ? The worker tried to walk out the area were he thought my brother should in this huge pile of dirt but there was no markings of any kind for him to be sure . He guessed and area and  stuck a flower there . We were very hurt and confused.  When I confronted the office about my concerns,  they gave several excuses as to why that area still looked like that after 5 months and tried to assure me he was over under all that pile of dirt according to there map?
I asked after they remove the pile dirt could they dig down enough for me to see the top of my brothers casket and there response was for $500.00. I don't  feel that's  right or fair since they do not have any markings to show me exactly where my brother is after 5 months !
**My suggestion if you bury a love one there make sure you see them lower your love one in the ground and you put a mark on it then.
Personally I would never ever bury someone there again.
The Cemetery is a nice place and has been kept well
However it was bought by another a new owner a li before my brothers (quote " burial ") And under new ownership is the reason why  the service has changed from what other people who buried their love ones there in the past have experience !

I don't like this place my mother b Buried there a few months ago and they marked a grave but now I can't found her office always close. This is so heartbreaking I can't mark her grave because I don't know where she at .

There are some true works of art here, some of the deadly departed didn't spare a penny on their graveside icons.
The summer is THE best time to visit any cemetery. A++++

reviews.text: I brought a burial from Indiana to Our Redeemer Cemetery.  Very much appreciated the friendliness and helpfulness of the guys at the cemetery.

Just called the office.  Mom was buried January 2020, dirt on grave site and missing soil under headstone.  Was informed grass seed will be applied and grave site to be maintained .  Why did I need to make this call.  And what is all the debris at the back of the cemetery..within viewing of my parents headstone..   My grandparents are buried here; never had this problem before.

Our Redeemer Cemetery is where both of my parents are buried.  It is supposed to be a perpetual care cemetery, "perpetual" meaning that the grave sites are kept well groomed under an endowment given to the cemetery to maintain the plots or graves in accordance with the law.
When my father died, I was astounded by how unkept the cemetery was.  There were so many graves that were obscured by long weeds and grass.   I took many photos of how badly obscured grave sites were and will post later.  I would not bury your loved one here.

What has happened to this cemetery? Both of my parents are buried here and it gets worse looking by the year. It has an abandoned look to it. This was suppose to be perpetual care, but this place is a perpetual mess and has been for years now.This needs to be legally addressed. It's horrible.

reviews.text: My brother Rick passed unexpectedly on 10-22-19.  It has been sad and painful especially for my 87 1/2 year old Mother to burying her son.  They were more than accommodating to us.  They made things better at this time of sorrow and easy for our family.  I appreciate their kindness and attention. Thank you so much.  Rick is resting in Peace now.
I spoke to the executive manager and he was very helpful. I'm glad my grandparents are here.
MacKenzie

reviews.text: We are so grateful to Norrisa at Oak Grove for her kind and knowledgeable assistance with the recent loss of our brother. Every call was compassionately handled and her assistance with the service was so appreciated.  Oak Grove was a mess when we laid our mother to rest in 2013, and while there is still a lot of work to do, the new owners have made great improvements to the chapel and grounds.
Can’t wait to see my old man my grandpa Dr.Gabriel I love you so much grandpa thank you Kim I love you too.

I just want to say that the staff was absolutely amazing!  I walked in and was greeted immediately.  I was looking for where my aunt was buried and she knew exactly where she was! I was amazed with how well they know their stuff.  She was so friendly! I wish there was more like her. We had some good conversations.  I didn’t get her name but I hope she reached her jazmine Sullivan water goals
I was appalled by the way the Oak Grove staff treated our group. Overt hostility, swearing at the funeral director, making threats. In 20 years as a pastor, I've never seen ANYTHING like this.
Debbie Anderson, that young man was me. I need to be contacted by people from the Mausoleum . The families of the people in there. Its very important...Very Important
